latestIgtvVideos.caption:
AMAN VS WILD : SPOTTED OWLETS! Can you SPOT THEM behind me!?

Trying a new format of introducing wildlife to people - SHOW THIS TO YOUR KIDS, and ask them if they’ve ever seen these beautiful owls flying around their neighbourhood or colony at night!?

Coming to you from Bharatpur Bird Sanctuary with 5 sleepy visitors joining us! Have you ever seen the spotted owlets before?

At the end, I’ve included a photo from my camera too for better quality! ( the audio is clear as I used an external mic and raised it to 200% during post processing, no birds were disturbed! 😊)

Bharatpur is wonderful as a family holiday destination for wildlife - so visit! 🌅

latestIgtvVideos.title: PLASTIC FREE JULY
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Did you know about a SILENT KILLER in our midst - ALUMINUM FOIL!?

Aluminium foil is actually worse for the environment than even plastic wraps as it includes mining for aluminium which causes deforestation and loss of wildlife and the resources & energy then needed to transport the materials. 

So, WHAT DO WE DO? Well, turn to Beeswax - biodegradable, eco friendly and a great alternative to aluminium or plastic wraps!

Thank you @be.ecological for sending me the amazing Beeswax food wraps! Check them out to get your sustainable daily items and create positive environmental impact! 

Let me know in the comments on any ways you are sustainable in your life! ♻️ 

It’s time we all go the green way, and make conscious decisions that are good for planet, and people.
For the present, and the future generations!

Music: Outside by @iksonmusic

latestIgtvVideos.title: PLASTIC FREE JULY : How to travel sustainably
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hi everyone, it’s #PlasticFreeJuly, so here are my 3 tips to travel sustainability and ditch single use plastics!

1. Reusable and metal cutlery > disposable cutlery
2. Copper/Glass bottle > Plastic water bottles
3. Bamboo toothbrush > Plastic toothbrush

Thank you @be.ecological for sending me the amazing reusable and metal cutlery and bottle and the bamboo toothbrush! Check them out to get your sustainable daily items and create positive environmental impact! 

Let me know in the comments on any ways you are sustainable in your life that I may have missed out on  mentioning! ♻️ 

It’s time we all go the green way, and make conscious decisions that are good for planet, and people.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Delhi MONSOON On My ORGANIC TERRACE GARDEN!!!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
.
Can you believe this is Delhi???

The Delhi Monsoons first rain is here, and my plants are loving it!

So I decided to make a video of me fake struggling to pick up fallen plants (😜🤫) and showing you a bit of my terrace garden! 
Delhi looks new and wonderful with this coat of rain! 💧🌈💫

I have about 400 huge pots of different food and flowering plants growing, from watermelon and guava to tomatoes and pomegranates! Living in an urban city, I make the best use of the space I have on my terrace and have managed to create a garden where I can grow my own food as well as which attracts bees and butterflies! 🦋🐝

latestIgtvVideos.title: Cancel Board Exams
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
As our country reels under the effects of a deadly pandemic, our system is still considering sending kids to sit for offline physical boards during this time.

CBSE has shown that it’s priorities are the marksheet and the 12th grade exams, not the health, safety and lives of students!

1.4 Million Indian students sit for the CBSE board exams. Acc to census, an average Indian family has about 5 members. That means the conduction of one single exam would impact a total of almost 8-10 Million people, including children, teachers, workers, staff and their families!

Our lives are not expendable and cannot be collateral damage for holding these exams. The loss of life and health cannot be acceptable losses for the system. Mental health is a non existent word in India.

The system must be held accountable, and board exams must be cancelled in the offline mode with an internal assessment method followed. For those extremely small percent of students who  aren’t happy with their marks, they should be allowed to sit for the exam as and when the situation allows so.
@ndtv @gargirawat

latestIgtvVideos.title: Thousands Of Slender-Billed Gull And Flamingo Eggs Destroyed For Road
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
#repost @indiatimesinsta 

This is disgusting, shocking and sad.

A heart wrenching video has surfaced from Gujarat showing the destruction of a nesting colony of Slender-Billed Gulls and Greater Falmingos. 

In fact the slender billed gulls nesting in that part was not common and had happened due to a good monsoon, but the contractor bulldozed the nesting colony, killing about 5000 eggs/chicks!

The video was shot from Greater Rann of Kutch near Khavda village of Kutch district and was posted on Twitter by Anish Andheria, CEO-Wildlife Conservation Trust.

According to local reports, the migratory birds had laid eggs on a patch that was allocated for road construction last year, but the work had been stopped for a long time.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Now This
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Thank you @nowthisnews  @nowthisearth for this lovely video on my work!!

Co-founding the Cuckoo about nature club was an experience in building a family and community of nature lovers amongst kids, and I am proud of where we have reached with it. Writing my first book was an experience I will never forget.

I’m constantly learning, growing, loving - more reading, more writing, more shooting - every day spent in nature is non-stop yet fun education received in the lap of Mother Earth. 

Thank you to you all for being so supportive, encouraging and action oriented as a community engaging with me constantly for a better chance at a better planet and a better future. I hope I keep growing everyday and learning new things everyday, with you and from you!

PS: I’m 17 :)

latestIgtvVideos.title: Brain Drain @indiatimesinsta
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hi everyone, these are just my personal views and reasons of choosing to study at UPenn from a perspective of pursuing environmental studies (not IT, AI, medical) as of now and getting a well rounded education. I have spent 15 years studying in India and looking forward to the next 4 in the US, then coming back hopefully to create some change with a new perspective and approach. Indian unis are also great for those who want to pursue them - this is in no way a diss on Indian unis but rather my opinion on the Indian education system overall, especially in schools. 

Also for a lot of Indians studying abroad is a matter of finances, privilege and opportunity. I did touch on these topics and the economic gap in the whole 1 hour interview along with the positives of the Indian education system but since the posts version is only 5minutes as a short clip, you may not hear all my opinions. 

Wishing you all best of luck for your college admissions too 💚🪴

@upenn2025

FOLLOW FOR MORE❤️MOM & I met some birds enjoying the rains! ❤️ This Monsoon, even birds love getting drenched, enjoying the water puddles and having a blast! Birds love water just as much as we do, and these rains are the perfect excuse for them to show off their lovely colours, wings and even behaviours! Let’s keep a bowl of water out for birds at our home, be it in the summer, winter or even monsoon :)

Some videos all thanks to @incrediblebirding, at their property in Sattal, who’ve been doing tours across the world and have the best sightings! Khushboo and Rahul, thank you for ensuring I always get to see the most amazing birds! Email them at info@incrediblebirding.com and plan a tour with them at the best birding lodge with 250+ species in a year 💚

latestPosts.caption:
Got back to Art after SO LONG. Once I got into wildlife photography and then college, art took a back seat- I didn’t have time for my hobby anymore. This last week however I promised to do one painting a day in my free time, and here’s the result, + some pictures from childhood of ARTIST ME 😊

As a child, when I had no access to mobile phones and laptops, I used to draw the birds I saw from my balcony so I could remember what they looked like. I would then take my drawings to the library, and using a book on birds cross check the names!

Laughter, excitement and curiosity are what I remember most from those times
the fondest of memories in having my
creativity peak and ooze out of my fingers
onto the world with nature as my inspiration.
To manifest my artwork into something
delightful and beautiful. The world around was my muse, and also my canvas. Nature and birds have taught me so much more than alot of classes in school have.

To be patient. Kind. Empathetic. Caring.
The child in me will always be alive when I'm
out in the wild, free and spirited, young and
glowing!

latestPosts.caption:
Happy WORLD PHOTOGRAPHY DAY!!❤️Here’s our 20 favourite pictures from the last 8 years!!!! 😊🦚🐯 

Whenever I tell people most of the birds I photograph are from India, they often look at me in disbelief! It’s hard for them to believe our country has birds as beautiful and stunning as these. But it does! It’s 1300+ bird species are colourful, diverse and mostly, breathtaking.

Before travelling to Africa for safari, we might want to discover what our own country has, or our city, or even our own backyards! 

For me, connections start at home. Stop waiting for a big holiday so you can travel to national parks, and start exploring your urban ecosystems! Trust me, you’ll be surprised! 💚

*Butterfly added in lion pic
